column1: #Text=The New York Knicks ( 8 - 10 ) defeated the Houston Rockets ( 7 - 10 ) 111 - 111 on Wednesday at Madison Square Garden in New York .
#Text=The Knicks got off to a quick start in this one , out - scoring the Knicks 25 - 21 in the first quarter alone .

#Text=The Rockets were the superior shooters in this game , going 58 percent from the field and 33 percent from the three - point line , while the Rockets went 58 percent from the floor and 33 percent from beyond the arc .

#Text=The Knicks were led by Arron Afflalo , who went 13 - for - 19 from the field and 2 - for - 4 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 31 points , while also adding seven rebounds and three assists .
#Text=It was his second straight game with a career - high of 31 points ( 13 - 19 FG , 2 - 4 3Pt , 3 - 4 FT ) of his own , while also adding seven rebounds .
#Text=It was his second double - double in a row , as he 000s combined for 45 points and 10 rebounds over his last two games .
#Text=Kristaps Porzingis was the only other starter in double figures , finishing with 20 points ( 8 - 13 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) , 13 rebounds and two blocked shots .
#Text=The Rockets 000 next game will be on the road against the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday , while the Knicks will travel to Charlotte to play the Hornets on Wednesday .
